REGIONAL MAP TRACKER -- SKYRIM, HOLD BY HOLD
Snapshot: post-Riften / post-Forelhost, mid-prep (see "post riften" doc).
Purpose: read a hold's entry when the cart enters it. Each entry: who
holds it, what the party sees riding through, dangers, trade, and live
hooks. Update after every gate choice and clock advance.
Visual companion: "skyrim world map.svg" in this folder.

GLOBAL CONDITIONS (apply everywhere unless a hold says otherwise)
  Prices: goods +50%, food +75%. Caravans between warring holds have
    stopped; checkpoints on every major road.
  Thalmor warrants: party, Krusp, Esbern -- standing Suspicion/disguise
    rule in Imperial-aligned holds (Solitude, Whiterun, Markarth).
  Rumor weather: false-flag paranoia. Strangers are suspected agents;
    inns ask which side you sell to before they ask your name.

=====================================================================
THE RIFT  (Riften, Ivarstead, Forelhost ruin, Thornheart Grove)
=====================================================================
CONTROL: Stormcloak-aligned, functionally Maven Black-Briar's.
WHAT THE PARTY SEES: Riften celebrates -- golden light, market chatter,
  notices thanking the Lanterns and Danica for the Grove. The city is
  safe and oblivious; the apocalypse is elsewhere. Danica works the
  Temple of Mara in a hauberk; Krusp stands its door.
DANGERS: Thieves Guild in the shadows; Maven's eyes everywhere; the
  poisoned-well aftermath keeps Ivarstead hostile to strangers (the
  planted Shadowmark has locals blaming the Guild).
SITES:
  Forelhost -- lab destroyed by the party. The fortress stands looted
    and quiet; Rahgot's garrison is gone north with Antoine.
  Ivarstead -- frightened twice over: the well, and now the mountain.
    Klimmek drinks at the inn instead of climbing. Foot of Fire B.
  Thornheart Grove -- cleansed (Act I); the notice-board version credits
    Danica and the Lanterns.
TRADE: best-supplied hold the party will see; Maven's monopolies keep
  shelves stocked at the inflated standard.
LIVE HOOKS: Grelod/Honorhall [PENDING finale]. Maven's patronage
  [PENDING]. Balimund's forge investment [PENDING].
GM-ONLY FUSE (background rot -- never a quest hook): Mila's mother
  carries Alfonso's strain, incubating. When it matures she reinfects
  Riften with a worse plague than the meadery affair; she dies alone
  beneath the sewers. Nobody is left to fight it (party gone, Danica
  with Krusp, Antoine at Bleak Falls). Maven and the Jarl recognize
  Windhelm's disease and copy its doctrine -- seal the Warrens, write
  off the city below. ATTRIBUTION IS HANDLED IN-FICTION: the dying
  Stormcloak courier at the Bee and Barb becomes the official source
  -- the man who came begging for help is posthumously blamed for
  the outbreak. Nobody looks further. Deliver as texture in Riften
  news; the party caused it twice over and does not know. See
  Npcs/Mila, Section IV.

=====================================================================
EASTMARCH  (Windhelm, Kynesgrove, Darkwater Crossing, Eldergleam)
=====================================================================
CONTROL: Stormcloak heartland -- and the war's open wound.
WHAT THE PARTY SEES: refugee columns moving away from three separate
  ruins: Kynesgrove (dragon), Darkwater (roots), Windhelm (plague).
  Grey, brittle forest where the pines were green. Woodsmoke off
  Windhelm with a sweet stench under it.
DANGERS: plague camps outside Windhelm's barred gates -- restoration
  magic FEEDS the disease; a healer in those camps is a vector. Hostile
  spriggans and mutated beasts in all deep forest. The corruption's dead
  zone around Darkwater widens along the river.
SITES:
  Windhelm -- SEALED. Galmar holds the inner barricades; Ulfric behind
    closed doors; the Afflicted Conclave's hidden Peryite shrine inside
    the Gray Quarter. Gate 3 Fire A.
  Darkwater Crossing -- consumed. Roots own the town; the mine is a
    tomb. The Corrupted Taproot still beats underneath.
  Kynesgrove -- massacre site of the Awakening; Sahloknir's empty mound.
  Eldergleam Sanctuary -- inverted into a font of corruption (Gate 1
    failure); a hostile dungeon and the rot's main body.
TRADE: collapsed. Food moves under armed escort or it is robbed.
LIVE HOOKS: Galmar's dying runner begs Davinia. Hroki contract waits
  inside the sealed city. Conclave scripture = Alfonso's phylactery lead.

=====================================================================
THE PALE  (Dawnstar, Fort Dunstad approach, the northern coast)
=====================================================================
CONTROL: DRAGON CULT. Vokun's occupied fortress-city.
WHAT THE PARTY SEES (from a distance -- nobody sees it close and
  reports back): a city with shut gates, lit by nothing, patrolled in
  formation. Wreckage of the Stormcloak siege camp under fresh snow.
DANGERS: organized draugr patrols with horn signals; Vaermina nightmare
  field over the city (sleeping near Dawnstar risks psychic damage);
  half-buried plague dead from the Cohort's collapse.
SITES:
  Dawnstar -- the raised Jarl sits the longhouse as Vokun's thrall.
    Northern anchor of the Cult; staging ground for Tier 2.
  Fort Dunstad -- still garrisoned by the living. HELD BEAT: Vokun takes
    it AFTER the party claims the Dragonstone (Tier 2 trigger).
TRADE: none. The coast road is abandoned.
LIVE HOOKS: Frostflow Lighthouse resistance status unknown -- decide
  when relevant. Silus Vesuius and the Razor shards (Gate 4 material).

=====================================================================
WHITERUN HOLD  (Whiterun, Riverwood, Bleak Falls Barrow)
=====================================================================
CONTROL: Neutral under Balgruuf -- an isolated economic island, squeezed
  by both armies and by Nahkriin's burned-farm frame job.
WHAT THE PARTY SEES: fortified checkpoints, grain wagons under guard,
  a city taking in refugees it cannot feed at +75%.
DANGERS: Imperial-aligned patrols (standing Suspicion rule); Thalmor
  presence thickening around Riverwood -- gold-eyed patrols watching the
  barrow road, hunting Davinia.
SITES:
  Bleak Falls Barrow -- the Dragonstone sleeps under a draugr garrison
    THAT NOW HOSTS Antoine and Ulag, fallen back from Forelhost with
    Rahgot's backing. A delve target hardening into a Cult strongpoint
    behind a Thalmor blockade. Gate 3 Fire C, escalating.
  Riverwood -- barricaded and paranoid; first town in the path if the
    barrow garrison spills downhill.
TRADE: functioning but rationed; the only neutral market left standing.
LIVE HOOKS: Esbern's commission. The Word Wall in the deep barrow.
  THE ECHO MIMIC IS HERE -- bound to Ulag as his deathlords were, it
  travels with him. A delve into the barrow walks the party into
  Kyboh's copy with no warning.

=====================================================================
THE THROAT OF THE WORLD  (Ivarstead approach, 7,000 Steps, High Hrothgar)
=====================================================================
CONTROL: contested between silence and the Dagon Cult.
WHAT THE PARTY SEES: Waystones bleeding black sap, station by station.
  Grey robes and horn-and-fire faces above the third shrine. Air that
  loses the order of moments -- a dropped stone lands before it falls.
DANGERS: temporal distortion hazards thicken with altitude; cultist
  ambushes from the rocks; the root network under the mountain is dying
  and the path dies with it.
SITES:
  High Hrothgar -- the Greybeards hold the summit by Voice alone,
    exhausted, supplies cut. They will not come down.
  The Time-Wound -- Gaelen the Root-Twister's true target: widen
    Alduin's tear and let the Unmaking through. Gate 3 Fire B.
TRADE: one provisioner made this climb weekly. He has stopped.
LIVE HOOKS: Saijah's migraine is a compass. Klimmek's undelivered
  supplies are a door-opener with the Greybeards.

=====================================================================
WINTERHOLD  (the College, the Sea of Ghosts, the Singing Glacier)
=====================================================================
CONTROL: nominal Jarl; the College is the only real power.
WHAT THE PARTY SEES: the broken cliff-town as they left it; scholars
  buying Dwemer salvage at war prices.
DANGERS: the coast north of town belongs to whatever Hjolmar wants on
  it. Sea travel is the only safe approach and it is not safe.
SITES:
  The College -- future Dagon target (Ancano/the Eye; Rising Tides
    material). Urag would pay well for Tower Protocol context.
  The Singing Glacier -- Hjolmar's seat, wearing Kyboh's body. The pull
    north the party feels lands here. The trap of the Personal Path.
TRADE: thin, ship-borne, expensive.
LIVE HOOKS: GEAR's tonal log points here and says "you could go there."
  Nora's soul-vessel research has College implications.

=====================================================================
HJAALMARCH  (Morthal, the marsh)
=====================================================================
CONTROL: Imperial-aligned, in name. In practice: locked doors.
WHAT THE PARTY SEES: a town that survived the party's bargain and knows
  something fed elsewhere because of a deal struck in the dark. Shutters
  close when strangers pass. Children are walked indoors.
DANGERS: hostility, watchfulness, and a militia quick to escort
  outsiders to the road. Old feeding grounds in the marsh.
LIVE HOOKS: the Morthal consequence is a debt with no collector yet.
  If the party ever needs Hjaalmarch's help, this is the price of the
  Valerius bargain coming due.

=====================================================================
HAAFINGAR  (Solitude, Dragon Bridge)
=====================================================================
CONTROL: Imperial capital; Tullius preparing the eastern push.
WHAT THE PARTY SEES (if they dare the gates): banners, drill squares,
  a war economy running hot -- and Thalmor in pairs on every third
  street. The Suspicion rule bites hardest here.
DANGERS: General Caelinus's network is alerted to Davinia's movements.
  Thalmor headquarters. Valerius's court rising beneath the politics.
SITES:
  The Blue Palace -- Elisif's court, the future Dark Coronation stage.
  Castle Dour -- Tullius, Caelinus, and the warrant desk.
TRADE: best-stocked market in Skyrim, at the standard inflation, for
  customers who can survive being looked at.
LIVE HOOKS: Valerius's blackmail dossier (the tax collectors). The
  Emperor contract gathering in Brotherhood channels. Davinia's father.

=====================================================================
THE REACH  (Markarth)
=====================================================================
CONTROL: Imperial-aligned; the Forsworn frame job has the hold at a
  rolling boil.
WHAT THE PARTY SEES: a murdered Dibella priestess's city looking for
  someone to hang; native Reachfolk rounded up on planted evidence.
DANGERS: Suspicion rule; mob justice; actual Forsworn answering the
  crackdown with real raids now.
LIVE HOOKS: the false-flag evidence (ancient Nord killing wounds, wrong
  tracks) is still in that temple for anyone who looks. Otar sleeps
  under the Reach -- Rising Tides material, not yet live.

=====================================================================
FALKREATH HOLD  (Falkreath, the southern pines)
=====================================================================
CONTROL: nominal Jarl; the forest is the real story.
WHAT THE PARTY SEES: ash-grey pine stands spreading from the east;
  hunters selling mutated pelts they cannot explain; beasts with extra
  eyes and fired hides.
DANGERS: corrupted wildlife; the Dagon rot's southern finger.
LIVE HOOKS: Sanguine Sanctum (Act I site). The Bloodmoon Hunt and the
  Razor's Falkreath beats live in Gate 4 -- seeds only for now.

